"129.8.242.109","CVE-2012-2687","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"2.6","2.6","2.0","Multiple cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities in the make_variant_list function in mod_negotiation.c in the mod_negotiation module in the Apache HTTP Server 2.4.x before 2.4.3, when the MultiViews option is enabled, allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via a crafted filename that is not properly handled during construction of a variant list.","0.0466","0.89594","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
