"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4025","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"7.5","7.5","2.0","PHP before 5.4.41, 5.5.x before 5.5.25, and 5.6.x before 5.6.9 truncates a pathname upon encountering a \x00 character in certain situations, which allows remote attackers to bypass intended extension restrictions and access files or directories with unexpected names via a crafted argument to (1) set_include_path, (2) tempnam, (3) rmdir, or (4) readlink.  NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2006-7243.","0.07947","0.92278","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
