"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4116","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"9.8","7.5","3.0","Use-after-free vulnerability in the spl_ptr_heap_insert function in ext/spl/spl_heap.c in PHP before 5.5.27 and 5.6.x before 5.6.11 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code by triggering a failed SplMinHeap::compare operation.","0.03291","0.87532","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4147","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"7.5","7.5","2.0","The SoapClient::__call method in ext/soap/soap.c in PHP before 5.4.39, 5.5.x before 5.5.23, and 5.6.x before 5.6.7 does not verify that __default_headers is an array, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code by providing crafted serialized data with an unexpected data type, related to a ""type confusion"" issue.","0.47996","0.978","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4148","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"5.0","5.0","2.0","The do_soap_call function in ext/soap/soap.c in PHP before 5.4.39, 5.5.x before 5.5.23, and 5.6.x before 5.6.7 does not verify that the uri property is a string, which allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information by providing crafted serialized data with an int data type, related to a ""type confusion"" issue.","0.11836","0.9391","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4598","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"6.5","7.5","3.0","PHP before 5.4.42, 5.5.x before 5.5.26, and 5.6.x before 5.6.10 does not ensure that pathnames lack %00 sequences, which might allow remote attackers to read or write to arbitrary files via crafted input to an application that calls (1) a DOMDocument save method or (2) the GD imagepsloadfont function, as demonstrated by a filename\0.html attack that bypasses an intended configuration in which client users may write to only .html files.","0.00675","0.72049","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4599","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"9.8","10.0","3.0","The SoapFault::__toString method in ext/soap/soap.c in PHP before 5.4.40, 5.5.x before 5.5.24, and 5.6.x before 5.6.8 allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information, cause a denial of service (application crash), or possibly execute arbitrary code via an unexpected data type, related to a ""type confusion"" issue.","0.06568","0.91389","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4600","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"9.8","10.0","3.0","The SoapClient implementation in PHP before 5.4.40, 5.5.x before 5.5.24, and 5.6.x before 5.6.8 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly execute arbitrary code via an unexpected data type, related to ""type confusion"" issues in the (1) SoapClient::__getLastRequest, (2) SoapClient::__getLastResponse, (3) SoapClient::__getLastRequestHeaders, (4) SoapClient::__getLastResponseHeaders, (5) SoapClient::__getCookies, and (6) SoapClient::__setCookie methods.","0.10739","0.93525","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4601","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"9.8","10.0","3.0","PHP before 5.6.7 might allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly execute arbitrary code via an unexpected data type, related to ""type confusion"" issues in (1) ext/soap/php_encoding.c, (2) ext/soap/php_http.c, and (3) ext/soap/soap.c, a different issue than CVE-2015-4600.","0.21375","0.95843","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
