"129.8.242.109","CVE-2015-4604","80","tcp","Apache httpd","2.2.15",,"7.5","5.0","3.0","The mget function in softmagic.c in file 5.x, as used in the Fileinfo component in PHP before 5.4.40, 5.5.x before 5.5.24, and 5.6.x before 5.6.8, does not properly maintain a certain pointer relationship, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly execute arbitrary code via a crafted string that is mishandled by a ""Python script text executable"" rule.","0.09106","0.92874","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","ipeer.ts.fresnostate.edu,ipeer.ad.csufresno.edu","fresnostate.edu,csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-16T18:41:56.040453"
