"129.8.242.44","CVE-2007-2768","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"4.3","4.3","2.0","OpenSSH, when using OPIE (One-Time Passwords in Everything) for PAM, allows remote attackers to determine the existence of certain user accounts, which displays a different response if the user account exists and is configured to use one-time passwords (OTP), a similar issue to CVE-2007-2243.","0.00189","0.40805","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2008-3844","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"9.3","9.3","2.0","Certain Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) 4 and 5 packages for OpenSSH, as signed in August 2008 using a legitimate Red Hat GPG key, contain an externally introduced modification (Trojan Horse) that allows the package authors to have an unknown impact.  NOTE: since the malicious packages were not distributed from any official Red Hat sources, the scope of this issue is restricted to users who may have obtained these packages through unofficial distribution points.  As of 20080827, no unofficial distributions of this software are known.","0.02746","0.86366","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2016-20012","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.3","4.3","3.0","OpenSSH through 8.7 allows remote attackers, who have a suspicion that a certain combination of username and public key is known to an SSH server, to test whether this suspicion is correct. This occurs because a challenge is sent only when that combination could be valid for a login session. NOTE: the vendor does not recognize user enumeration as a vulnerability for this product","0.08647","0.92656","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2017-15906","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","The process_open function in sftp-server.c in OpenSSH before 7.6 does not properly prevent write operations in readonly mode, which allows attackers to create zero-length files.","0.02659","0.86161","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2018-15473","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","OpenSSH through 7.7 is prone to a user enumeration vulnerability due to not delaying bailout for an invalid authenticating user until after the packet containing the request has been fully parsed, related to auth2-gss.c, auth2-hostbased.c, and auth2-pubkey.c.","0.90356","0.9962","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2018-15919","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","Remotely observable behaviour in auth-gss2.c in OpenSSH through 7.8 could be used by remote attackers to detect existence of users on a target system when GSS2 is in use. NOTE: the discoverer states 'We understand that the OpenSSH developers do not want to treat such a username enumeration (or ""oracle"") as a vulnerability.'","0.02082","0.8441","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2018-20685","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.3","2.6","3.0","In OpenSSH 7.9, scp.c in the scp client allows remote SSH servers to bypass intended access restrictions via the filename of . or an empty filename. The impact is modifying the permissions of the target directory on the client side.","0.03377","0.87694","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2019-6109","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"6.8","4.0","3.0","An issue was discovered in OpenSSH 7.9. Due to missing character encoding in the progress display, a malicious server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can employ crafted object names to manipulate the client output, e.g., by using ANSI control codes to hide additional files being transferred. This affects refresh_progress_meter() in progressmeter.c.","0.09738","0.93139","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2019-6110","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"6.8","4.0","3.0","In OpenSSH 7.9, due to accepting and displaying arbitrary stderr output from the server, a malicious server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can manipulate the client output, for example to use ANSI control codes to hide additional files being transferred.","0.57569","0.98208","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2019-6111","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.9","5.8","3.0","An issue was discovered in OpenSSH 7.9. Due to the scp implementation being derived from 1983 rcp, the server chooses which files/directories are sent to the client. However, the scp client only performs cursory validation of the object name returned (only directory traversal attacks are prevented). A malicious scp server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can overwrite arbitrary files in the scp client target directory. If recursive operation (-r) is performed, the server can manipulate subdirectories as well (for example, to overwrite the .ssh/authorized_keys file).","0.53643","0.98052","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2020-14145","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.9","4.3","3.0","The client side in OpenSSH 5.7 through 8.4 has an Observable Discrepancy leading to an information leak in the algorithm negotiation. This allows man-in-the-middle attackers to target initial connection attempts (where no host key for the server has been cached by the client). NOTE: some reports state that 8.5 and 8.6 are also affected.","0.01254","0.79839","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2020-15778","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"7.4","6.8","3.0","scp in OpenSSH through 8.3p1 allows command injection in the scp.c toremote function, as demonstrated by backtick characters in the destination argument. NOTE: the vendor reportedly has stated that they intentionally omit validation of ""anomalous argument transfers"" because that could ""stand a great chance of breaking existing workflows.""","0.64277","0.9847","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2021-36368","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"3.7","2.6","3.0","An issue was discovered in OpenSSH before 8.9. If a client is using public-key authentication with agent forwarding but without -oLogLevel=verbose, and an attacker has silently modified the server to support the None authentication option, then the user cannot determine whether FIDO authentication is going to confirm that the user wishes to connect to that server, or that the user wishes to allow that server to connect to a different server on the user's behalf. NOTE: the vendor's position is ""this is not an authentication bypass, since nothing is being bypassed.","0.00432","0.63235","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2021-41617","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"7.0","4.4","3.0","sshd in OpenSSH 6.2 through 8.x before 8.8, when certain non-default configurations are used, allows privilege escalation because supplemental groups are not initialized as expected. Helper programs for AuthorizedKeysCommand and AuthorizedPrincipalsCommand may run with privileges associated with group memberships of the sshd process, if the configuration specifies running the command as a different user.","0.00274","0.5124","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2023-38408","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"9.8",,"3.0","The PKCS#11 feature in ssh-agent in OpenSSH before 9.3p2 has an insufficiently trustworthy search path, leading to remote code execution if an agent is forwarded to an attacker-controlled system. (Code in /usr/lib is not necessarily safe for loading into ssh-agent.) NOTE: this issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2016-10009.","0.64352","0.98474","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2023-48795","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"5.9",,"3.0","The SSH transport protocol with certain OpenSSH extensions, found in OpenSSH before 9.6 and other products, allows remote attackers to bypass integrity checks such that some packets are omitted (from the extension negotiation message), and a client and server may consequently end up with a connection for which some security features have been downgraded or disabled, aka a Terrapin attack. This occurs because the SSH Binary Packet Protocol (BPP), implemented by these extensions, mishandles the handshake phase and mishandles use of sequence numbers. For example, there is an effective attack against SSH's use of ChaCha20-Poly1305 (and CBC with Encrypt-then-MAC). The bypass occurs in chacha20-poly1305@openssh.com and (if CBC is used) the -etm@openssh.com MAC algorithms. This also affects Maverick Synergy Java SSH API before 3.1.0-SNAPSHOT, Dropbear through 2022.83, Ssh before 5.1.1 in Erlang/OTP, PuTTY before 0.80, AsyncSSH before 2.14.2, golang.org/x/crypto before 0.17.0, libssh before 0.10.6, libssh2 through 1.11.0, Thorn Tech SFTP Gateway before 3.4.6, Tera Term before 5.1, Paramiko before 3.4.0, jsch before 0.2.15, SFTPGo before 2.5.6, Netgate pfSense Plus through 23.09.1, Netgate pfSense CE through 2.7.2, HPN-SSH through 18.2.0, ProFTPD before 1.3.8b (and before 1.3.9rc2), ORYX CycloneSSH before 2.3.4, NetSarang XShell 7 before Build 0144, CrushFTP before 10.6.0, ConnectBot SSH library before 2.2.22, Apache MINA sshd through 2.11.0, sshj through 0.37.0, TinySSH through 20230101, trilead-ssh2 6401, LANCOM LCOS and LANconfig, FileZilla before 3.66.4, Nova before 11.8, PKIX-SSH before 14.4, SecureCRT before 9.4.3, Transmit5 before 5.10.4, Win32-OpenSSH before 9.5.0.0p1-Beta, WinSCP before 6.2.2, Bitvise SSH Server before 9.32, Bitvise SSH Client before 9.33, KiTTY through 0.76.1.13, the net-ssh gem 7.2.0 for Ruby, the mscdex ssh2 module before 1.15.0 for Node.js, the thrussh library before 0.35.1 for Rust, and the Russh crate before 0.40.2 for Rust.","0.51662","0.97963","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2023-51385","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"6.5",,"3.0","In ssh in OpenSSH before 9.6, OS command injection might occur if a user name or host name has shell metacharacters, and this name is referenced by an expansion token in certain situations. For example, an untrusted Git repository can have a submodule with shell metacharacters in a user name or host name.","0.18499","0.95409","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2023-51767","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"7.0",,"3.0","OpenSSH through 10.0, when common types of DRAM are used, might allow row hammer attacks (for authentication bypass) because the integer value of authenticated in mm_answer_authpassword does not resist flips of a single bit. NOTE: this is applicable to a certain threat model of attacker-victim co-location in which the attacker has user privileges. NOTE: this is disputed by the Supplier, who states ""we do not consider it to be the application's responsibility to defend against platform architectural weaknesses.""","7.0E-5","0.0049","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2025-26465","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"6.8",,"3.0","A vulnerability was found in OpenSSH when the VerifyHostKeyDNS option is enabled. A machine-in-the-middle attack can be performed by a malicious machine impersonating a legit server. This issue occurs due to how OpenSSH mishandles error codes in specific conditions when verifying the host key. For an attack to be considered successful, the attacker needs to manage to exhaust the client's memory resource first, turning the attack complexity high.","0.61222","0.98352","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2025-32728","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"4.3",,"3.0","In sshd in OpenSSH before 10.0, the DisableForwarding directive does not adhere to the documentation stating that it disables X11 and agent forwarding.","0.0022","0.44865","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2026-35385","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"7.5",,"3.0","In OpenSSH before 10.3, a file downloaded by scp may be installed setuid or setgid, an outcome contrary to some users' expectations, if the download is performed as root with -O (legacy scp protocol) and without -p (preserve mode).","6.7E-4","0.21072","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2026-35386","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"3.6",,"3.0","In OpenSSH before 10.3, command execution can occur via shell metacharacters in a username within a command line. This requires a scenario where the username on the command line is untrusted, and also requires a non-default configurations of % in ssh_config.","4.0E-4","0.12456","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2026-35387","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"3.1",,"3.0","OpenSSH before 10.3 can use unintended ECDSA algorithms. Listing of any ECDSA algorithm in PubkeyAcceptedAlgorithms or HostbasedAcceptedAlgorithms is misinterpreted to mean all ECDSA algorithms.","6.1E-4","0.19422","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2026-35388","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"2.5",,"3.0","OpenSSH before 10.3 omits connection multiplexing confirmation for proxy-mode multiplexing sessions.","1.7E-4","0.04498","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.44","CVE-2026-35414","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.4",,"4.2",,"3.0","OpenSSH before 10.3 mishandles the authorized_keys principals option in uncommon scenarios involving a principals list in conjunction with a Certificate Authority that makes certain use of comma characters.","3.6E-4","0.11047","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id4.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-03.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-14T10:37:17.708056"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2007-2768","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"4.3","4.3","2.0","OpenSSH, when using OPIE (One-Time Passwords in Everything) for PAM, allows remote attackers to determine the existence of certain user accounts, which displays a different response if the user account exists and is configured to use one-time passwords (OTP), a similar issue to CVE-2007-2243.","0.00189","0.40353","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2008-3844","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"9.3","9.3","2.0","Certain Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) 4 and 5 packages for OpenSSH, as signed in August 2008 using a legitimate Red Hat GPG key, contain an externally introduced modification (Trojan Horse) that allows the package authors to have an unknown impact.  NOTE: since the malicious packages were not distributed from any official Red Hat sources, the scope of this issue is restricted to users who may have obtained these packages through unofficial distribution points.  As of 20080827, no unofficial distributions of this software are known.","0.02746","0.86051","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-0777","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"6.5","4.0","3.0","The resend_bytes function in roaming_common.c in the client in OpenSSH 5.x, 6.x, and 7.x before 7.1p2 allows remote servers to obtain sensitive information from process memory by requesting transmission of an entire buffer, as demonstrated by reading a private key.","0.67203","0.98576","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-0778","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"8.1","4.6","3.0","The (1) roaming_read and (2) roaming_write functions in roaming_common.c in the client in OpenSSH 5.x, 6.x, and 7.x before 7.1p2, when certain proxy and forward options are enabled, do not properly maintain connection file descriptors, which allows remote servers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact by requesting many forwardings.","0.01092","0.7805","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-10009","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.3","7.5","3.0","Untrusted search path vulnerability in ssh-agent.c in ssh-agent in OpenSSH before 7.4 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary local PKCS#11 modules by leveraging control over a forwarded agent-socket.","0.01579","0.81659","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-10010","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.0","6.9","3.0","sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4, when privilege separation is not used, creates forwarded Unix-domain sockets as root, which might allow local users to gain privileges via unspecified vectors, related to serverloop.c.","9.0E-4","0.25265","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-10011","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.5","2.1","3.0","authfile.c in sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4 does not properly consider the effects of realloc on buffer contents, which might allow local users to obtain sensitive private-key information by leveraging access to a privilege-separated child process.","1.6E-4","0.03732","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-10012","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.8","7.2","3.0","The shared memory manager (associated with pre-authentication compression) in sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4 does not ensure that a bounds check is enforced by all compilers, which might allows local users to gain privileges by leveraging access to a sandboxed privilege-separation process, related to the m_zback and m_zlib data structures.","2.1E-4","0.05944","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-10708","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.5","5.0","3.0","sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and daemon crash) via an out-of-sequence NEWKEYS message, as demonstrated by Honggfuzz, related to kex.c and packet.c.","0.0312","0.86907","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-1907","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","The ssh_packet_read_poll2 function in packet.c in OpenSSH before 7.1p2 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and application crash) via crafted network traffic.","0.00564","0.68448","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-1908","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"9.8","7.5","3.0","The client in OpenSSH before 7.2 mishandles failed cookie generation for untrusted X11 forwarding and relies on the local X11 server for access-control decisions, which allows remote X11 clients to trigger a fallback and obtain trusted X11 forwarding privileges by leveraging configuration issues on this X11 server, as demonstrated by lack of the SECURITY extension on this X11 server.","0.02179","0.84433","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-20012","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.3","4.3","3.0","OpenSSH through 8.7 allows remote attackers, who have a suspicion that a certain combination of username and public key is known to an SSH server, to test whether this suspicion is correct. This occurs because a challenge is sent only when that combination could be valid for a login session. NOTE: the vendor does not recognize user enumeration as a vulnerability for this product","0.14603","0.94501","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-3115","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"6.4","5.5","3.0","Multiple CRLF injection vulnerabilities in session.c in sshd in OpenSSH before 7.2p2 allow remote authenticated users to bypass intended shell-command restrictions via crafted X11 forwarding data, related to the (1) do_authenticated1 and (2) session_x11_req functions.","0.47105","0.97701","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2016-8858","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.5","7.8","3.0","The kex_input_kexinit function in kex.c in OpenSSH 6.x and 7.x through 7.3 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption) by sending many duplicate KEXINIT requests.  NOTE: a third party reports that ""OpenSSH upstream does not consider this as a security issue.""","0.26866","0.96384","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2017-15906","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","The process_open function in sftp-server.c in OpenSSH before 7.6 does not properly prevent write operations in readonly mode, which allows attackers to create zero-length files.","0.03174","0.87013","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2018-15473","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","OpenSSH through 7.7 is prone to a user enumeration vulnerability due to not delaying bailout for an invalid authenticating user until after the packet containing the request has been fully parsed, related to auth2-gss.c, auth2-hostbased.c, and auth2-pubkey.c.","0.90356","0.99607","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2018-15919","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.3","5.0","3.0","Remotely observable behaviour in auth-gss2.c in OpenSSH through 7.8 could be used by remote attackers to detect existence of users on a target system when GSS2 is in use. NOTE: the discoverer states 'We understand that the OpenSSH developers do not want to treat such a username enumeration (or ""oracle"") as a vulnerability.'","0.02073","0.8404","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2018-20685","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.3","2.6","3.0","In OpenSSH 7.9, scp.c in the scp client allows remote SSH servers to bypass intended access restrictions via the filename of . or an empty filename. The impact is modifying the permissions of the target directory on the client side.","0.03377","0.87431","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2019-6109","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"6.8","4.0","3.0","An issue was discovered in OpenSSH 7.9. Due to missing character encoding in the progress display, a malicious server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can employ crafted object names to manipulate the client output, e.g., by using ANSI control codes to hide additional files being transferred. This affects refresh_progress_meter() in progressmeter.c.","0.09738","0.9297","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2019-6110","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"6.8","4.0","3.0","In OpenSSH 7.9, due to accepting and displaying arbitrary stderr output from the server, a malicious server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can manipulate the client output, for example to use ANSI control codes to hide additional files being transferred.","0.57569","0.9818","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2019-6111","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.9","5.8","3.0","An issue was discovered in OpenSSH 7.9. Due to the scp implementation being derived from 1983 rcp, the server chooses which files/directories are sent to the client. However, the scp client only performs cursory validation of the object name returned (only directory traversal attacks are prevented). A malicious scp server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can overwrite arbitrary files in the scp client target directory. If recursive operation (-r) is performed, the server can manipulate subdirectories as well (for example, to overwrite the .ssh/authorized_keys file).","0.54405","0.98042","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2020-14145","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.9","4.3","3.0","The client side in OpenSSH 5.7 through 8.4 has an Observable Discrepancy leading to an information leak in the algorithm negotiation. This allows man-in-the-middle attackers to target initial connection attempts (where no host key for the server has been cached by the client). NOTE: some reports state that 8.5 and 8.6 are also affected.","0.01562","0.81578","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2020-15778","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.4","6.8","3.0","scp in OpenSSH through 8.3p1 allows command injection in the scp.c toremote function, as demonstrated by backtick characters in the destination argument. NOTE: the vendor reportedly has stated that they intentionally omit validation of ""anomalous argument transfers"" because that could ""stand a great chance of breaking existing workflows.""","0.64277","0.98458","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2021-36368","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"3.7","2.6","3.0","An issue was discovered in OpenSSH before 8.9. If a client is using public-key authentication with agent forwarding but without -oLogLevel=verbose, and an attacker has silently modified the server to support the None authentication option, then the user cannot determine whether FIDO authentication is going to confirm that the user wishes to connect to that server, or that the user wishes to allow that server to connect to a different server on the user's behalf. NOTE: the vendor's position is ""this is not an authentication bypass, since nothing is being bypassed.","0.00432","0.62703","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2021-41617","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.0","4.4","3.0","sshd in OpenSSH 6.2 through 8.x before 8.8, when certain non-default configurations are used, allows privilege escalation because supplemental groups are not initialized as expected. Helper programs for AuthorizedKeysCommand and AuthorizedPrincipalsCommand may run with privileges associated with group memberships of the sshd process, if the configuration specifies running the command as a different user.","0.00274","0.507","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2023-38408","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"9.8",,"3.0","The PKCS#11 feature in ssh-agent in OpenSSH before 9.3p2 has an insufficiently trustworthy search path, leading to remote code execution if an agent is forwarded to an attacker-controlled system. (Code in /usr/lib is not necessarily safe for loading into ssh-agent.) NOTE: this issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2016-10009.","0.64352","0.98461","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2023-48795","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"5.9",,"3.0","The SSH transport protocol with certain OpenSSH extensions, found in OpenSSH before 9.6 and other products, allows remote attackers to bypass integrity checks such that some packets are omitted (from the extension negotiation message), and a client and server may consequently end up with a connection for which some security features have been downgraded or disabled, aka a Terrapin attack. This occurs because the SSH Binary Packet Protocol (BPP), implemented by these extensions, mishandles the handshake phase and mishandles use of sequence numbers. For example, there is an effective attack against SSH's use of ChaCha20-Poly1305 (and CBC with Encrypt-then-MAC). The bypass occurs in chacha20-poly1305@openssh.com and (if CBC is used) the -etm@openssh.com MAC algorithms. This also affects Maverick Synergy Java SSH API before 3.1.0-SNAPSHOT, Dropbear through 2022.83, Ssh before 5.1.1 in Erlang/OTP, PuTTY before 0.80, AsyncSSH before 2.14.2, golang.org/x/crypto before 0.17.0, libssh before 0.10.6, libssh2 through 1.11.0, Thorn Tech SFTP Gateway before 3.4.6, Tera Term before 5.1, Paramiko before 3.4.0, jsch before 0.2.15, SFTPGo before 2.5.6, Netgate pfSense Plus through 23.09.1, Netgate pfSense CE through 2.7.2, HPN-SSH through 18.2.0, ProFTPD before 1.3.8b (and before 1.3.9rc2), ORYX CycloneSSH before 2.3.4, NetSarang XShell 7 before Build 0144, CrushFTP before 10.6.0, ConnectBot SSH library before 2.2.22, Apache MINA sshd through 2.11.0, sshj through 0.37.0, TinySSH through 20230101, trilead-ssh2 6401, LANCOM LCOS and LANconfig, FileZilla before 3.66.4, Nova before 11.8, PKIX-SSH before 14.4, SecureCRT before 9.4.3, Transmit5 before 5.10.4, Win32-OpenSSH before 9.5.0.0p1-Beta, WinSCP before 6.2.2, Bitvise SSH Server before 9.32, Bitvise SSH Client before 9.33, KiTTY through 0.76.1.13, the net-ssh gem 7.2.0 for Ruby, the mscdex ssh2 module before 1.15.0 for Node.js, the thrussh library before 0.35.1 for Rust, and the Russh crate before 0.40.2 for Rust.","0.53559","0.98005","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2023-51385","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"6.5",,"3.0","In ssh in OpenSSH before 9.6, OS command injection might occur if a user name or host name has shell metacharacters, and this name is referenced by an expansion token in certain situations. For example, an untrusted Git repository can have a submodule with shell metacharacters in a user name or host name.","0.16522","0.94929","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2023-51767","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.0",,"3.0","OpenSSH through 10.0, when common types of DRAM are used, might allow row hammer attacks (for authentication bypass) because the integer value of authenticated in mm_answer_authpassword does not resist flips of a single bit. NOTE: this is applicable to a certain threat model of attacker-victim co-location in which the attacker has user privileges. NOTE: this is disputed by the Supplier, who states ""we do not consider it to be the application's responsibility to defend against platform architectural weaknesses.""","7.0E-5","0.0047","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2025-26465","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"6.8",,"3.0","A vulnerability was found in OpenSSH when the VerifyHostKeyDNS option is enabled. A machine-in-the-middle attack can be performed by a malicious machine impersonating a legit server. This issue occurs due to how OpenSSH mishandles error codes in specific conditions when verifying the host key. For an attack to be considered successful, the attacker needs to manage to exhaust the client's memory resource first, turning the attack complexity high.","0.73977","0.98844","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2026-35385","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"7.5",,"3.0","In OpenSSH before 10.3, a file downloaded by scp may be installed setuid or setgid, an outcome contrary to some users' expectations, if the download is performed as root with -O (legacy scp protocol) and without -p (preserve mode).","4.2E-4","0.12689","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2026-35386","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"3.6",,"3.0","In OpenSSH before 10.3, command execution can occur via shell metacharacters in a username within a command line. This requires a scenario where the username on the command line is untrusted, and also requires a non-default configurations of % in ssh_config.","3.3E-4","0.09364","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2026-35387","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"3.1",,"3.0","OpenSSH before 10.3 can use unintended ECDSA algorithms. Listing of any ECDSA algorithm in PubkeyAcceptedAlgorithms or HostbasedAcceptedAlgorithms is misinterpreted to mean all ECDSA algorithms.","3.7E-4","0.10913","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2026-35388","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"2.5",,"3.0","OpenSSH before 10.3 omits connection multiplexing confirmation for proxy-mode multiplexing sessions.","1.3E-4","0.02138","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
"129.8.242.42","CVE-2026-35414","22","tcp","OpenSSH","7.0",,"4.2",,"3.0","OpenSSH before 10.3 mishandles the authorized_keys principals option in uncommon scenarios involving a principals list in conjunction with a Certificate Authority that makes certain use of comma characters.","2.2E-4","0.06249","false","false","California State University at Fresno","California State University at Fresno","AS2037","id2.cs.csufresno.edu,openstack-01.csm.csufresno.edu","csufresno.edu",,"US","Fresno","2026-06-04T08:08:53.403928"
